<p>I have a table in MySQL like this:</p>  <pre><code>+-------+----------+ |  am   | ipiresia | +-------+----------+ | 50470 |       29 | | 50470 |       43 | | 50433 |       29 | |  6417 |       51 | |  6417 |       52 | |  6417 |       53 | |  4960 |       25 | |  4960 |       26 | |  5567 |       89 | |  6716 |       88 | +-------+----------+ </code></pre>  <p>I want to transform it like this:</p>  <pre><code>+-------+-----------+-----------+-----------+ |  am   | ipiresia1 | ipiresia2 | ipiresia3 | +-------+-----------+-----------+-----------+ | 50470 |        29 |        43 |           | | 50433 |        29 |           |           | |  6417 |        51 |        52 |        53 | |  4960 |        25 |        26 |           | |  5567 |        89 |           |           | |  6716 |        88 |           |           | +-------+-----------+-----------+-----------+ </code></pre>  <p>Of course this is only a part of the table. The max occurrences of 'ipiresia' per 'am' can be up to 5, so I think a dynamic pivot table could do the work but I don't know how to do it.</p>